-- Iran to Name Candidate for OPEC Chief Role, Donya-e-Eqtesad Says
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-05-29T15:22:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/iran-to-name-candidate-for-opec-chief-role-donya-e-eqtesad-says.html
Iran  will name a candidate for the
job of OPEC secretary general when the producer group meets next
month,  Donya-e-Eqtesad  reported, citing the nation’s governor to
the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries.  Mohammad Ali Khatibi didn’t identify a person for the role,
according to the Tehran-based newspaper. Iran is OPEC’s second-
biggest producer after  Saudi Arabia .  The group’s current secretary-general, Libya’s Abdalla el- Badri, will end his second three-year term at the end of this
year. Ministers from OPEC’s 12 member states plan to gather at
its headquarters in Vienna on June. 14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi via Dubai at 
